<br>
First, the characters. A more motley crew of misfits and rogues I have never seen!<br>
Squall: The moody, anti-social guy that dresses in black and carries a sword. Check!<br>
Rinoa: Two-dimensional lover girl. Check!<br>
Selphie: Perhaps the least fleshed out character, ever, in any FF. Hell, Umaro got more then her.<br>
Quistis: Naughty school teacher with a whip. Gotcha!<br>
Zell: The second most fleshed out character.<br>
Irvine: The egomaniac who.. &lt;gasp&gt; IS NERVOUS! Who woulda thought?<br>
Laguna: Guess what? No backstory here either!<br>
Kyros and Ward: I would have remembered more about these characters, but they blur into pixelated hell.<br>
I can vaguely remember a couple other characters, but they're so completely cookie-cutter I can't even remember them.<br>
<br>
Also, FF8 Introduces the innovate DRAW combat system, the most thought out and well reasoned system of combat since Square gave a rhesus monkey a computer! But how does it work, you ask? Can I still summon Knights of the Round 20 times in a row? No, but do have a variety of exciting summons, which each come with a complimentary marathon animation that Squaresoft, in all its benevolence, has made impossible to turn off. Because what could be more fun then watching 45 seconds of explosions and roaring every time you wanted to do 5k damage? Can I still spam Ultima, you cry? Your characters can't LEARN spells, no, no, no. You have to steal them from monsters! And it gets better. Casting spells? Your characters can't do that without using these summon things. Use items? Nope, can't do that either without the aid of a big fish-thing. Wipe their asses? Well, the jury's still out on this one, but I'm guessing Squall has to have Ifrit equipped and junction Ultima to 'bunghole' after a quick trip to porcelain paradise.<br>
<br>
The story has so many exciting twists and turns! You're betrayed by someone you thought a friend! &lt;gasp&gt; You're imprisoned! &lt;choke&gt; The enemy at the beginning of the game ISN'T THE FINAL ENEMY! &lt;faint&gt; And, in fact, all the characters are from the SAME ORPHANAGE - which they've all conveniently forgotten! My nipples tingle with excitement! And you get to go into space! And generic lovergirl and generic antisocial guy fall in love! It makes my heart stop. Oh, wait, that's just my will to live fading merely recalling this game.<br>
<br>
